cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the development of methods for automatic text summarization. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the evaluation of automatic summaries is a key task in this field. Additionally, the use of keyphrases and their lemma form in the matching process suggests a possible connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the application of the system to evaluate different summaries of Arabic multi-document data set presented at TAC2011 suggests a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
